Vietnam Stock Movers: Ninh Hoa Sugar, Refrigeration Electrical

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-26T05:46:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/vietnam-stock-movers-ninh-hoa-sugar-refrigeration-electrical.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Vietnam  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11 a.m. local-time close.  The VN Index, the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, climbed 3 percent to 398.04, snapping 10 days of
declines. The gauge yesterday slumped 4 percent to the lowest
close since May 14, 2009.       Ninh Hoa Sugar Joint-Stock Co. (NHS VN) increased 4.2
percent to 32,300 dong, the biggest advance since May 16. The
company will pay its shareholders a dividend of 2,500 dong a
share on July 4, according to a statement on the bourse’s
website.  Vietnam Electricity Construction Joint-Stock Co. (VNE VN),
which offers construction services for electricity system
projects, and industrial and construction projects, rose 3.9
percent to 5,300 dong, the most since April 25. The company will
buy back 1 million shares within three months, starting from
June 1.  Vietnam’s  Refrigeration Electrical Engineering Corp. (REE)  , known as REE, advanced 4.2 percent to 10,000 dong, the most
since March 11. Ho Chi Minh City-based REE plans to buy back 10
million shares from June 1 until Dec. 31, it said in a statement
filed to the exchange’s website.  --Nguyen Kieu Giang. Editor: Darren Boey  To contact the Bloomberg News Staff on this story:
